[[2010 Campeonato Ecuatoriano de F\u00fatbol Serie A|2010]]\n\n;[[Toronto FC]]\n*[[Canadian Championship]] (2): [[2011 Canadian Championship|2011]], [[2012 Canadian Championship|2012]]\n\n;[[Real Salt Lake]]\n*[[Major League Soccer]] Western Conference Championship (1): [[2013 Major League Soccer season|2013]], [[2014 Major League Soccer season|2014]]\n\n===Individual===\n*[[George Gross Memorial Trophy]]: 2011\n*[[Red Patch Boys#Player of the year award|Red Patch Boys Player of the Year]]: 2011<ref>{{cite web|url=http://redpatchboys.ca/about/player-awards/|title=RFB Toronto FC \"Man of the Year\" Award|publisher=redpatchboys.ca|accessdate=1 July 2018}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{MLS|joao-plata}}\n*{{NFT player|43439}}\n*[http://www.ecuafutbol.org/web/modal.php?cedula=0921915526 FEF card] {{in lang|es}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Plata, Joao}}\n[[Category:1992 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Association football wingers]]\n[[Category:Designated Players (MLS)]]\n[[Category:Ecuador international footballers]]\n[[Category:Ecuadorian expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Ecuadorian expatriate sportspeople in the United States]]\n[[Category:Ecuadorian footballers]]\n[[Category:Ecuadorian Serie A players]]\n[[Category:Expatriate soccer players in Canada]]\n[[Category:Expatriate soccer players in the United States]]\n[[Category:L.D.U. Quito footballers]]\n[[Category:Major League Soccer players]]\n[[Category:Real Salt Lake players]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Guayaquil]]\n[[Category:Toronto FC draft picks]]\n[[Category:Toronto FC players]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use mdy dates|date=March 2015}}\n{{Infobox football biography \n|name                 = Joao Plata\n|image                = Joao_Plata5-25-13_Fire-171-1.JPG\n|image_size           = 250\n|caption              = Plata playing against the [[Chicago Fire SC|Chicago Fire]] on May 25, 2013\n|fullname             = Joao Jimmy Plata Cotera\n|birth_date           = {{birth date and age|1992|03|01}}\n|birth_place          = [[Guayaquil]], Ecuador\n|height               = {{convert|1.57|m|abbr=on}}\n|position             = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]]\n|currentclub          = \n|clubnumber           = \n|youthyears1          = 2004\u20132007\n|youthclubs1          = [[Barcelona Sporting Club|Barcelona SC]]\n|youthyears2          = 2007\u20132009\n|youthclubs2          = Alfaro Moreno\n|youthyears3          = 2009\u20132010\n|youthclubs3          = [[Liga Deportiva Universitaria de Quito|LDU Quito]]\n|years1               = 2010\u20132011\n|clubs1               = [[LDU Quito]]\n|caps1                = 7\n|goals1               = 1\n|years2               = 2011\n|clubs2               = \u2192 [[Toronto FC]] (loan)\n|caps2                = 26\n|goals2               = 3\n|years3               = 2012\n|clubs3               = [[Toronto FC]]\n|caps3                = 10\n|goals3               = 0\n|years4               = 2012\n|clubs4               = \u2192 [[LDU Quito]] (loan)\n|caps4                = 13\n|goals4               = 1\n|years5               = 2013\u20132019\n|clubs5               = [[Real Salt Lake]]\n|caps5                = 175\n|goals5               = 46\n|nationalyears1       = 2011\u2013\n|nationalteam1        = [[Ecuador national football team|Ecuador]]\n|nationalcaps1        = 5\n|nationalgoals1       = 2\n|medaltemplates       =\n|club-update          = October 18, 2019\n|nationalteam-update  = October 16, 2018\n}}\n{{spanish name|Plata|Cotera}}\n'''Joao Jimmy Plata Cotera''' ({{IPA-es|jo\u02c8au \u02c8plata}};<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vxcTWmSrCGg Ras Tas Tas with Joao Plata & Olmes Garcia | The Real World]</ref> born March 1, 1992) is an Ecuadorian [[Association football|footballer]] who last played for [[Real Salt Lake]] in [[Major League Soccer]] as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]].\n\n==Club career==\n\n===LDU Quito===\nPlata began his career in the youth ranks of hometown club [[Barcelona Sporting Club|Barcelona]] before joining the Alfaro Moreno Academia in Guayaquil in 2009.<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20110903173005/http://www.alfaromoreno.com/noticias.php?id=74 \"Joao Plata y su debut\"]. alfaromoreno.com.</ref> After impressing at Alfaro Moreno he joined the youth ranks of [[Liga Deportiva Universitaria de Quito|LDU Quito]].<ref>[http://www.diario-extra.com/ediciones/2010/10/03/deportes/joao-plata-un-salsero--en-la-cancha/ \"Extra.ec \u2013 Joao Plata un salsero  en la cancha\"]. diario-extra.com. October 3, 2010</ref>\n\nPlata impressed Liga coach [[Edgardo Bauza]] and was called up to the senior side during the Second Stage of the [[2010 Campeonato Ecuatoriano de F\u00fatbol Serie A|2010 Serie A]] season. On August 22, 2010 Plata made his professional debut for [[Liga Deportiva Universitaria de Quito|LDU Quito]] at [[Estadio de Liga Deportiva Universitaria|Estadio Casa Blanca]] in a 1\u20130 victory over [[Centro Deportivo Olmedo|Olmedo]]. His debut was considered very promising and Plata became a fixture for the rest of the season.<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20120315212123/http://www.futbolinmediato.com/index.php?module=Noticias&func=noticia&id=28680&umt=una_excelente_primera_impresion Una excelente primera impresi\u00f3n]. futbolinmediato.com. August 24, 2010</ref>\n\nOn September 18, 2010 Plata scored his first professional goal in a 1\u20130 victory over [[Club Deportivo ESPOLI|ESPOLI]]. This important goal helped Liga consolidate their position at the top of the table.<ref>[http://www.liguistas.com/index.php?itemid=1307 \"Liga Deportiva Universitaria \u2013 Liga de Quito; Un sitio de hinchas Liguistas para hinchas Liguistas\"]. liguistas.com.</ref><ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20120308215338/http://www.ecuavisa.com/deporte-nacional/28585.html Joao Plata: Estoy contento y esperemos seguir as\u00ed]. ecuavisa.com. September 21, 2010</ref> Plata ended the season appearing in 7 league matches (starting 5) and scoring one goal as Liga captured the Second Stage of the [[2010 Campeonato Ecuatoriano de F\u00fatbol Serie A|2010 Serie A]] and then defeated [[Club Sport Emelec|Emelec]] to be declared national champion for the 10th time in the club's history.\n\n===Toronto FC===\nAt the conclusion of the 2010 season, in order to continue his development, Plata was loaned to [[Major League Soccer]] and was selected by [[Toronto FC]] with the No. 49 pick in the [[2011 MLS SuperDraft]].<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20110830162707/http://teradeportes.com/newsv2.php?id_noticia=36775 Joao Plata se suma a Estupi\u00f1an y Ganchoso en el sue\u00f1o americano (Audio)]. teradeportes.com. January 6, 2011</ref> Toronto FC signed Plata on March 24, 2011.<ref>[http://www.torontofc.ca/post/2011/03/24/toronto-fc-signs-stevanovic-and-plata \"Toronto FC Signs Stevanovic And Plata\"]. torontofc.ca. March 24, 2011</ref> On April 2 Plata made his debut for Toronto as a second half sub for [[Alen Stevanovi\u0107]], in a 1\u20131 home draw against [[C.D. Chivas USA|Chivas USA]].<ref>{{cite news |title= Gordon Goal Gifts Reds a Draw|url=http://www.torontofc.ca/news/2011/04/gordon-goal-gifts-reds-draw |publisher=Toronto FC |date=April 2, 2011 |accessdate=April 2, 2011 }}</ref> On April 27 Plata made his first start for Toronto and provided two assists in a 3\u20130 away win against [[FC Edmonton]] in the first leg of the [[Canadian Championship]].<ref>{{cite news |title= Toronto Takes A Stranglehold|url=http://www.torontofc.ca/news/2011/04/toronto-takes-stranglehold |publisher=Toronto FC |date=April 28, 2011 |accessdate=April 28, 2011 }}</ref> For the second leg on May 4, Plata again made the starting line-up and provided an assist as well as receiving Man of the Match honours in a 1\u20130 home win, giving Toronto a 4\u20130 aggregate victory over [[FC Edmonton]] to advance to the [[Canadian Championship]] final.<ref>{{cite news |title= Toronto Advances To NCC Final|url=http://www.torontofc.ca/news/2011/05/toronto-advances-ncc-final |publisher=Toronto FC |date=May 5, 2011 |accessdate=May 5, 2011 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Reds Rocket to NCC Final |url=http://www.torontofc.ca/content/reds-rocket-ncc-final |publisher=Toronto FC |date=May 4, 2011 |accessdate=May 4, 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110508223609/http://www.torontofc.ca/content/reds-rocket-ncc-final |archive-date=May 8, 2011 |url-status=dead }}</ref> Plata got his first MLS goal in a 2\u20131 victory over [[Houston Dynamo]] the goal was a well taken penalty and he later went on to set up the second for [[Maicon Santos]], his performance earned him MLS player of the week.<ref>[http://www.torontofc.ca/news/2011/05/joao-plata-named-player-week \"Joao Plata Named Player of the Week\"]. ''Toronto FC''. May 2011</ref> On July 2 Plata scored a crucial goal against [[Vancouver Whitecaps FC]] helping seal Toronto's third consecutive Canadian Championship, earning the team a berth in the [[CONCACAF Champions League]].<ref>{{cite news |title= Toronto FC wins 2011 Nutrilite Canadian Championship |url=http://canadasoccer.com/news/viewArtical.asp?Press_ID=4895 |publisher=Canada Soccer Association |date=July 2, 2011 |accessdate=July 9, 2011 }}</ref> Plata was awarded the [[George Gross Memorial Trophy]] as the tournament's best player.<ref>{{cite news |title=Plata wins 2011 George Gross Memorial Award |url=http://canadasoccer.com/news/viewArtical.asp?Press_ID=4896 |publisher=Canada Soccer Association |date=July 2, 2011 |accessdate=July 9, 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110805095526/http://www.canadasoccer.com/news/viewArtical.asp?Press_ID=4896 |archivedate=August 5, 2011 |df=mdy-all }}</ref> On July 27 Plata made his Champions League debut against [[Real Esteli F.C.]] coming on for [[Gianluca Zavarise]] in the 49th minute, Plata led his team to a 2\u20131 home victory scoring both goals.<ref>{{cite news |title= Plata Paces Toronto To Victory |url=http://www.torontofc.ca/news/2011/07/plata-paces-toronto-victory |publisher=Toronto FC |date=July 27, 2011 |accessdate=July 28, 2011 }}</ref> Plata's success continued in the champions league scoring two goals in a crucial match-up against [[FC Dallas]] on October 18 in the final group stage game, with a 3\u20130 away victory it advanced Toronto to its first ever quarter final appearance.<ref>{{cite news |title= Toronto tops Dallas to reach CCL quarters |url=http://www.concacaf.com/page/CL/NewsDetail/0,,12813~2486460,00.html |publisher=CONCACAF |date=October 18, 2011 |accessdate=October 19, 2011 }}</ref>\n\nOn January 11, 2012 the club announced a multi-year deal to keep Plata at Toronto FC; as per club policy and league, the details of the new contract signing were not disclosed, but reports suggest a $500,000 fee was paid to secure him.<ref>[http://www.canadiansoccernews.com/content.php?3138-Plata-s-transfer-fee \"Plata's transfer fee\"]. ''CSN''.</ref><ref>{{cite news |title= TFC Agree To Terms With Joao Plata |url=http://www.torontofc.ca/news/2012/01/tfc-agree-terms-joao-plata |publisher=TFC |date=January 10, 2012  }}</ref> Plata scored his first goal of the season on April 4, during the second leg of the [[2011\u201312 CONCACAF Champions League Championship Round|2011\u201312 CONCACAF Champions League semifinals]] against [[Santos Laguna]], Plata scored both goals in a 6\u20132 away loss.<ref>{{cite news |title= CCL: So Near Yet So Far |url=http://www.torontofc.ca/news/2012/04/ccl-so-near-yet-so-far |publisher=TFC |date=April 5, 2012 }}</ref>\n\nPlata returned to LDU Quito on a six-month loan from Toronto on July 11, 2012.<ref>[http://www.torontofc.ca/news/2012/07/plata-loan-deal-finalized \"Plata Loan Deal Finalized\"]. ''Toronto FC''. July 2012</ref>\n\n===Real Salt Lake===\nPlata re-joined Toronto in January 2013 upon the end of the loan.<ref>[http://www.mlssoccer.com/news/article/2013/01/24/platas-tfc-future-air-agent-tweets-he-may-join-rsl \"Plata's TFC future up in air; agent tweets he may join RSL\"]. MLSsoccer.com. January 24, 2013</ref> However, on January 30, 2013 he was traded to [[Real Salt Lake]] in exchange for a second-round pick in the [[2015 MLS SuperDraft]].<ref>[http://www.realsaltlake.com/news/2013/01/real-salt-lake-acquires-fw-joao-plata-toronto \"Real Salt Lake acquires FW Joao Plata from Toronto\"]. ''Real Salt Lake''. January 2013</ref>\n\nIn 2014, the Twitter hashtag #PlataEsOro became popular, a play on the meaning of Plata's name, \"plata\" being the Spanish word for \"silver\" and \"oro\" meaning \"gold.\" <ref>{{Cite web|url = https://twitter.com/RealSaltLake/status/462783495711244289|title = Real Salt Lake Twitter Account|date = May 3, 2014|accessdate = June 8, 2014|website = Twitter|publisher = Real Salt Lake}}</ref>\n\nHis contract option was declined by Real Salt Lake after the Salt Lake's [[2019 Real Salt Lake season|2019 season]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rsl.com/post/2019/11/21/rsl-announces-2020-roster-decisions|title=RSL Announces 2020 Roster Decisions|last=|first=|date=November 21, 2019|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=December 23, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nPlata was a member of the [[Ecuador national under-20 football team|Ecuador Under-20]] national team. On May 20, 2011 Plata was given his first senior call-up to the national team that will play in three friendlies between May 28 \u2013 June 7 that will help determine La Tricolor's final roster for this summer's Copa Am\u00e9rica.<ref>{{cite news |title= Plata Receives Ecuador Call |url=http://www.torontofc.ca/news/2011/05/plata-receives-ecuador-call |publisher=Toronto FC |date=May 21, 2011 |accessdate=May 22, 2011 }}</ref> Plata made his debut for the senior team against [[Canada men's national soccer team|Canada]], on June 1, 2011, as a second half sub in a 2\u20132 away draw, at his club team, [[Toronto FC]]'s home field [[BMO Field]].<ref>{{cite news |title= Joao Plata Makes Ecuador Debut|url=http://www.torontofc.ca/news/2011/06/joao-plata-makes-ecuador-debut |publisher=Toronto FC |date=June 1, 2011 |accessdate=June 4, 2011 }}</ref> Plata was called up for friendlies against the United States and El Slavador, in the game against El Salvador Plata scored two goals in a 5\u20131 win over El Salvador\n\n==Style of play==\nStanding at {{height|m=1.57}}, Plata is the shortest player in MLS history, alongside [[Cristian Techera]];<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mlssoccer.com/post/2014/10/02/joao-plata-stands-tall-mls-insider-presented-adidas|title=Joao Plata Stands Tall|publisher=MLS Soccer|date=2 October 2014|accessdate=2 May 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.whitecapsfc.com/players/cristian-techera |title=Cristian Techera |publisher=www.whitecapsfc.com |accessdate=12 November 2019 }}</ref> although not physically imposing, his small stature, combined with his low centre of gravity and resulting balance, make him extremely agile, and allow him to change direction very quickly in tight spaces, while his strong legs allow him to excel in short bursts of speed.<ref name=\"Real Salt Lake take first loss of 2016\">{{cite web|url=http://www.houstondynamo.com/post/2016/04/25/real-salt-lake-take-first-loss-2016-prior-matchup-against-houston-dynamo|title=Real Salt Lake take first loss of 2016 prior to matchup against Houston Dynamo|publisher=HoustonDynamo.com|date=25 April 2016|accessdate=2 May 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"Unique challenges await Seattle Sounders in first road trip of 2016\">{{cite web|url=http://www.soundersfc.com/post/2016/03/10/unique-challenges-await-seattle-sounders-first-road-trip-2016|title=Unique challenges await Seattle Sounders in first road trip of 2016|publisher=SoundersFC|author1=Will Parchman|date=10 March 2016|accessdate=2 May 2016}}</ref> In addition to his mobility and elusiveness, Plata is an extremely quick and dynamic player, who is known for his great acceleration over short distances, and his pace on the ball, as well as his [[Dribbling#Association football|dribbling]] ability and technical skills.<ref name=\"Real Salt Lake take first loss of 2016\"/><ref name=\"Unique challenges await Seattle Sounders in first road trip of 2016\"/><ref name=Profile>{{cite web|url=http://www.mlssoccer.com/players/joao-plata|title=Joao Plata - Profile|publisher=MLSSoccer.com|accessdate=2 May 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"Joao Plata emerging as true MLS star\">{{cite web|url=http://www.mlssoccer.com/post/2016/04/04/stejskal-real-salt-lakes-joao-plata-emerging-true-mls-star|title=Stejskal: Real Salt Lake's Joao Plata emerging as true MLS star|publisher=MLSSoccer.com|author1=Sam Stejskal|date=4 April 2016|accessdate=2 May 2016}}</ref> A creative forward, Plata is an accurate finisher, and is capable of both scoring and assisting goals, which allows him to play in several offensive positions: although he has been used as a striker or as a supporting forward, his favoured role is on the left wing, a position which allows him to move out wide to receive the ball, beat players on the dribble, and subsequently cut into the middle of the pitch on his stronger right foot to either shoot on goal or set up his teammates.<ref name=\"Real Salt Lake take first loss of 2016\"/><ref name=\"Unique challenges await Seattle Sounders in first road trip of 2016\"/><ref name=Profile/><ref name=\"Joao Plata emerging as true MLS star\"/>\n\n==Career statistics==\n{{updated|August 13, 2017|{{citation needed|date=June 2017}}}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|-\n! colspan=\"3\"| [[Ecuador]]\n! colspan=\"3\"| League\n! colspan=\"3\"| Playoffs\n! colspan=\"3\"| Domestic Cup\n! colspan=\"3\"| Continental\n! colspan=\"3\"| Total\n|-\n!Club\n!League\n!Season\n!Apps\n!Goals\n!Assists\n!Apps\n!Goals\n!Assists\n!Apps\n!Goals\n!Assists\n!Apps\n!Goals\n!Assists\n!Apps\n!Goals\n!Assists\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|[[Liga Deportiva Universitaria de Quito|LDU Quito]]\n| rowspan=\"1\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|[[