gua|2nd]] (20.9% of Nicaragua)\n| population_as_of = 2005\n| population_total = 306510\n| population_note = \n| population_blank1_title = Rank\n| population_blank1 = [[Departments of Nicaragua|7th]] (6.0% of Nicaragua)\n| population_density_km2  = auto\n| population_demonym = {{lang|es|Coste\u00f1o}} ({{abbr|m|masculine}}), {{lang|es|coste\u00f1a}} ({{abbr|f|feminine}})\n| population_footnotes = \n| postal_code_type = | postal_code = \n| area_code_type =\n| area_code =\n| geocode = \n| iso_code = [[ISO  3166-2:NI|NI-AS]]\n| blank_name_sec1  = Autonomy Statute\n| blank_info_sec1  = 30 October 1987\n| blank1_name_sec1 = [[Official language]]s\n| blank1_info_sec1 = '''National'''<br/>[[Spanish language|Spanish]]<br/><br/>'''Regional'''<br/>[[English-based creoles|Creole]] ''([[Miskito Coast Creole]] and [[Rama Cay Creole]])''<br/>[[Miskito language|Miskito]]<br/>[[Sumo languages|Sumo]] ''(Mayangna and Ulwa)''<br/>[[Garifuna language|Garifuna]]<br/>[[Rama language|Rama]]<br/>[[English language|English]]\n| blank2_name_sec1 = | blank2_info_sec1 = \n| blank_name_sec2  = Legislature\n| blank_info_sec2  = \n| blank1_name_sec2 = [[Autonomous Regional Council of the South Caribbean Coast|Regional Council]]\n| blank1_info_sec2 = 47 councilors\n| blank2_name_sec2 = [[National Assembly (Nicaragua)|National Assembly]]\n| blank2_info_sec2 = 2 deputies (of 92)\n| website =\n| footnotes = \n}}\n\nThe '''South Caribbean Coast Autonomous Region''' ({{lang-es|Regi\u00f3n Aut\u00f3noma de la Costa Caribe Sur}}, {{IPA-es|re\u02c8xjon aw\u02c8tonoma \u00f0e la \u02c8kosta ka\u02c8\u027ei\u03b2e su\u027e|pron}}), sometimes shortened to '''RACCS''', '''RACS''', or '''RAAS''' (for its former name, {{lang|es|Regi\u00f3n Aut\u00f3noma del Atl\u00e1ntico Sur}}), is one of two [[autonomous region]]s in [[Nicaragua]]. It covers an area of {{convert|27407|km2|abbr=on}} and has a population of 382,100 (2005 census). The capital is [[Bluefields]]. Bordering the [[Caribbean Sea]], it contains part of the region known as the [[Mosquito Coast]].\n\nThe [[Pearl Cays]] archipelago of islands is also a part of the South Caribbean Coast Autonomous Region.\n\n==See also==\n* {{Portal-inline|Nicaragua}}\n* [[North Caribbean Coast Autonomous Region]]\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://www.yorku.ca/cerlac/URACCAN/Coast.html The autonomous regions of Nicaragua's Caribbean Coast]\n* [http://www.minorityrights.org/?lid=969 From Conflict to Autonomy in Nicaragua: Lessons Learnt], report by Minority Rights Group International, April 2007\n{{Commons category|position=left|Regi\u00f3n Aut\u00f3noma de la Costa Caribe Sur}} \n{{NicaraguaDepartments}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:South Caribbean Coast Autonomous Region}}\n[[Category:South Caribbean Coast Autonomous Region]]\n[[Category:Autonomous regions of Nicaragua]]\n\n\n{{Nicaragua-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Autonomous region of Nicaragua}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name = South Caribbean Coast Autonomous Region\n| native_name = <small>{{lang|es|Regi\u00f3n Aut\u00f3noma de la Costa Caribe Sur}} {{in lang|es}}</small>\n| settlement_type = [[Autonomous region]]\n| image_skyline = | imagesize = | image_alt = | image_caption = \n| image_flag = Flag of Region Autonoma Atlantico Sur.svg\n| flag_size = \n| flag_alt = Flag of the South Caribbean Autonomous Region\n| image_shield = Seal of Region Autonoma del Atlantico Sur.svg\n| shield_size = 100px\n| shield_alt = Seal of the South Caribbean Autonomous Region\n| motto = \n| anthem = ''Himno de la Autonom\u00eda''\n| image_map = [[File:RAAS, Nicaragua.svg|200px|RACCS]]\n| map_caption = Location of the South Caribbean Autonomous Region in Nicaragua.\n| coordinates      = {{coord|12|0|N|83|45|W|region:NI-AS|display=inline,title}}\n| subdivision_type = Country\n| subdivision_name = [[Nicaragua]] <!-- No flags -->\n| seat_type = Capital\n| seat = [[Bluefields]]\n| subdivision_type1 = [[Largest city]]\n| subdivision_name1 = [[Bluefields]]\n| parts_type = [[Municipalities of Nicara